The paper proposes a new method based on recurrent-convolutional neural networks to automatically learn useful representations from segments of 4-D fMRI recordings for identifying patients with schizophrenia. This involves the use of machine learning techniques and neural networks, which are commonly associated with the following arXiv CS sub-categories: cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Therefore, these are the 5 most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
